    {
        "desc": "When stepped upon, this balcony complains with a stern creak. However built with\nthick logs running into the south wall, the planks are thin and brittle and the\nwhole structure leans slightly downwards. A slender railing runs along its edge,\nbut there is reasonable doubt whether it would support the weight of more than a\nsmall dog. A large wooden dome lies northwards and beneath you, with a platform\nin the middle. A thick rope is fastened in a hook just above the archway to the\nsouth, and passes over the platform to the barely visible opposite wall. A\nbasket hangs in a tackle from this thick rope. Another, thinner rope is attached\nto a small winch on the railing, with the other end attached to the basket. The\npoint seems to be to make a sensational entrance to the platform by flying in\nthe air standing in the basket.\n",
